# Debugging with GDB

1. Add -s -S Flag in QEmu 
    - -s starts a GDB server on port 1234.
    - -S stops the CPU until you connect via GDB.
2. Open two Ubuntu Terminal 
    - Run `image.iso` in first Terminal
    - Run `kernel.bin` which placed in iso_root/boot directory by `gdb kernel.bin`
    - Run `target remote:1234` in 2nd Terminal
3. To see inside of `init_gdb` by `break init_gdb`.


## References :
1. https://wiki.osdev.org/GDB
2. https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1471226/most-tricky-useful-commands-for-gdb-debugger
